{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.33",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 33,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 33",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 33 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:1",
      "text": "Hear therefore, O Job, my speeches, and hearken to all my words.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:2",
      "text": "Behold now I have opened my mouth, let my tongue speak within my jaws.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:3",
      "text": "My words are from my upright heart, and my lips shall speak a pure sentence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:4",
      "text": "The spirit of God made me, and the breath of the Almighty gave me life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:5",
      "text": "If thou canst, answer me, and stand up against my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:6",
      "text": "Behold God hath made me as well as thee, and of the same clay I also was formed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:7",
      "text": "But yet let not my wonder terrify thee, and let not my eloquence be burdensome to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:8",
      "text": "Now thou hast said in my hearing, and I have heard the voice of thy words:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:9",
      "text": "I am clean, and without sin: I am unspotted, and there is no iniquity in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:10",
      "text": "Because he hath found complaints against me, therefore he hath counted me for his enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:11",
      "text": "He hath put my feet in the stocks, he hath observed all my paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:12",
      "text": "Now this is the thing in which thou art not justified: I will answer thee, that God is greater than man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:13",
      "text": "Dost thou strive against him, because he hath not answered thee to all words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:14",
      "text": "God speaketh once, and repeateth not the selfsame thing the second time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:15",
      "text": "By a dream in a vision by night, when deep sleep falleth upon men, and they are sleeping in their beds:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:16",
      "text": "Then he openeth the ears of men, and teaching instructeth them in what they are to learn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:17",
      "text": "That he may withdraw a man from the things he is doing, and may deliver him from pride.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:18",
      "text": "Rescuing his soul from corruption: and his life from passing to the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:19",
      "text": "He rebuketh also by sorrow in the bed, and he maketh all his bones to wither.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:20",
      "text": "Bread becometh abominable to him in his life, and to his soul the meat which before he desired.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:21",
      "text": "His flesh shall be consumed away, and his bones that were covered shall be made bare.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:22",
      "text": "His soul hath drawn near to corruption, and his life to the destroyers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:23",
      "text": "If there shall be an angel speaking for him, one among thousands, to declare man's uprightness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:24",
      "text": "He shall have mercy on him, and shall say: Deliver him, that he may not go down to corruption: I have found wherein I may be merciful to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:25",
      "text": "His flesh is consumed with punishments, let him return to the days of his youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:26",
      "text": "He shall pray to God, and he will be gracious to him: and he shall see his face with joy, and he will render to man his justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:27",
      "text": "He shall look upon men, and shall say: I have sinned, and indeed I have offended, and I have not received what I have deserved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:28",
      "text": "He hath delivered his soul from going into destruction, that it may live and see the light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:29",
      "text": "Behold, all these things God worketh three times within every one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:30",
      "text": "That he may withdraw their souls from corruption, and enlighten them with the light of the living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:31",
      "text": "Attend, Job, and hearken to me, and hold thy peace, whilst I speak.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:32",
      "text": "But if thou hast any thing to say, answer me, speak: for I would have thee to appear just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.33.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 33,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 33:33",
      "text": "And if thou have not, hear me: hold thy peace, and I will teach thee wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
